# Statistics Centering Plan

## Goal Description
The user wants the statistics boxes to be centered within the "statistics frame". I interpret this as vertical centering within the `.detail-card` (which has a minimum height) and ensuring the boxes don't stretch to the full width, making them look like centered "boxes".

## Proposed Changes

### CSS Configuration
#### [MODIFY] [App.css](file:///c:/Users/admin/.gemini/%EC%8A%A4%EC%9C%84%EC%B9%98%EC%9B%B9%EC%84%9C%EB%B9%84%EC%8A%A4/daily-habit-tracker/src/App.css)
- Update `.detail-card`:
    - Add `justify-content: center`.
- Update `.stat-item`:
    - Remove `flex: 1`.
    - Add `width: 140px` (or similar fixed width/percentage that doesn't fill).
    - Maintain `display: flex` for internal content centering.

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
1.  Navigate to `/stats`.
2.  Verify that the statistics card contents are vertically centered.
3.  Verify that the "Active Habits" and "Total Checks" boxes are centered horizontally and have a defined width (not stretching to edges).
